TY  - JOUR
AU  - Golosov, Mikhail
AU  - Kocherlakota, Narayana
AU  - Tsyvinski, Aleh
T1  - Optimal Indirect and Capital Taxation
PY  - 2003
Y1  - 2003/07/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00256
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 70
IS  - 3
SP  - 569
EP  - 587
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We consider an environment in which agents' skills are private information and follow arbitrary stochastic processes. We prove that it is typically Pareto optimal for an individual's marginal benefit of investing in capital to exceed his marginal cost of doing so. This wedge is consistent with a positive tax on capital income. We also prove that it is Pareto optimal for the marginal rate of substitution between any two consumption goods to equal the marginal rate of transformation. This lack of a wedge is consistent with uniform taxation of consumption goods within a period.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00256
ER  - 



